   ```

2. The following citation in any derivative work or publication using this software:
   ```
   Johnson, T. C., R. J. Versteeg, A. Ward, F. D. Day-Lewis, and A. Revil (2010), 
   Improved hydrogeophysical characterization and monitoring through parallel modeling 
   and inversion of time-domain resistivity and induced polarization data, Geophysics, 
   75(4), Wa27-Wa41.

   Johnson TC, and DM Wellman. 2015. "Accurate modeling and inversion of electrical 
   resistivity data in the presence of metallic infrastructure with known location and 
   dimension." Geophysical Journal International 202(2):1096-1108. doi:10.1093/gji/ggv206.
   ```

